title: Aussie shares close higher
text:
Aussie shares close higher Print 
The Australian share market has closed one per cent higher, putting the Greek debt crisis to one side in the first session of the new financial year. 
At the close on Wednesday, the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was 56.7 points, or 1.04 per cent, higher at 5,515.7, while the broader All Ordinaries index was up 54.8 points, or 1.01 per cent, at 5,506.0, according to preliminary figures. 
On the ASX 24, the September share price index futures contract was 78 points higher at 5,475, with 30,498 contracts traded.   Terms
